A MAN has been airlifted to hospital with suspected serious injuries this morning after a two-vehicle crash in Aberdeenshire.
An air ambulance helicopter and emergency crews were scrambled to the accident scene at the A950-A891 junction near Brucklay Castle, Maud just after 6am.
The collision involved a blue Vito Mercedes van and blue B Series Mazda pick-up.
Police Scotland said the driver of the Mazda had to be cut free by firefighters using specialist cutting gear.
He was flown to Aberdeen Royal Infirmary. The driver of the Mercedes escaped with minor injuries.
The road is currently closed to traffic as a clear-up and crash examination takes place.

